cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses mechanized theorem proving and proof automation, which are core topics in logic and formal methods.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes using evolutionary computation to improve heuristics of automatic proof search.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as mechanized theorem proving is becoming the basis of reliable systems programming.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the Isabelle/HOL proof assistant, which is a programming language for expressing mathematical theories and proofs.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the challenge of discovering heuristics for automatic proof search, which can be seen as a problem in algorithm design.
